To develop a GUI we need to import tkinter library
Python 2: import Tkinter
Python 3: import tkinter

Import all from tkinter:
from tkinter import *

Create a window:
window = Tk()

Widgets are between the creation and the mainloop() method
Create a Button
b = Button(window, text="Execute")
To add a action to a button we define a function that will execute the action.
def hi():
  print("Hi!")
Then we add that function to the Button in the command parameter
b = Button(window, text="Execute", command=hi)


Adding a Widget to the window
b.pack or b.grid(row=y,column=x, rowspan=z)

Creating an entry
e = Entry(window)

To get a value from the entry we need to create a variable that will hold that value
just before we create the Entry Widget. This variable will store the StringVar() method
e_value = StringVar()
e       = Entry(window, textvariable=e_value)

To get the value from e_value, we apply the get() method
Creating a Text widget
height and width
t1 = Text(window, height=1, width=20)

To pass a value to a Text widgetwe use the insert method
t1.insert(END, )






window.mainloop()
